Arbor Day
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:OED2 orig. US A day set apart by law, orig. in the state of of Nebraska, afterwards observed throughout the US and adopted in Aust., Canada, and NZ, to be yearly observed for the planting of trees. 1872 Nebr. 1902 Aust 1967 NZ; W3
Origin:[none]
